# Physical Design Engineer - Job Descriptions

## JD 1 - Senior Physical Design Engineer (Analog Devices)

Key responsibilities include:

Own end-to-end physical implementation for major IP blocks and/or full-chip designs, ensuring alignment with career development framework.

Develop and optimize floorplans including macro placement, IO ring planning, power grid design, and congestion/area/timing analysis.

Execute place-and-route, clock tree synthesis, and timing closure using industry-standard tools like Cadence Innovus.

Perform detailed static timing analysis (STA) and drive sign-off across PVT corners and operating modes.

Identify and resolve physical verification issues (DRC/LVS/ERC) in close partnership with process/CAD/foundry teams.

Automate design flows to improve efficiency and quality; contribute to continuous flow enhancements.

Collaborate with RTL, DFT, verification, package, and library teams to meet performance, power, and area (PPA) targets.

Mentor and coach junior engineers, sharing best practices in physical design and advancing team capability.

Document methodologies and contribute to best practices, supporting a culture of learning and continuous improvement.

Demonstrate agility in adapting to changing business needs, leading by example, and striving for best-in-class results.

